proof: for F64 operands the generic binary_literal_op computes Literal::from_f64(float_op(from_bits(l), from_bits(r))) (out dtype F64 -> float branch); the fast path uses the exact same broadcast index math (flat_to_multi_into + broadcast_flat_index) and applies the same float_op, so element order and bits are identical, including -0.0+2.0 = 2.0 (index 1 bits differ since -0.0 is lhs), +inf-4.0 = +inf (index 2), NaN+5.0 = NaN (index 3, canonical). Non-F64Bits elements fall through to the generic path.
